<div id="readme">
<h2>Lucky Numbers!</h2>
<ul>

<li><strong>Use QWERTY in place of 123456</strong> </li>
<li></li>

<li><strong>High Concept:</strong>
Guessthe four-digit number based on clues given after each guess.
</li>

<li><strong>Player Experience Goals:</strong>
I want the player to feel frustration or determination.
</li>

<li><strong>Genre:</strong>
Arcade puzzle game!
</li>

<li><strong>Game play:</strong>
Choose numbers 1-6 using the QWERTY keys. After four numbers have been entered,
a hint will appear telling you how close your guess is to the right answer.
</li>

<li><strong>Prototype goal:</strong>
To figure out more about keyboard input reading as well as printing sprites
rather than text. 
</li>

<li><strong>Features:</strong>
The goal of figuring out the winning numbers the hacker's way.
</li>

<li><strong>Setting/Premise:</strong>
You are hacking the Lottery Company's database.
</li>

<li><strong>Story:</strong>
You are a troublemaking young adult that suddenly decides to have lots of money.
So, using your hacking skills, you break into the Lottery Company's database
and try to figure out the winning numbers before the security system notices you.
</li>

<li><strong>Target Audience:</strong>
People who like puzzle games.
</li>

<li><strong>Play time:</strong>
About five minutes.
</li>

<li><strong>Strategies:</strong>
Look for patterns in the hints that you recieve.
</li>

<li><strong>Prototype Assets:</strong>
All original.
</li>

<li><strong>Prototype Closest Other Game:</strong>
Mastermind.
</li>

</ul>
</div>
</body>
